370 REGISTRUM DE ABERBROTHOC.

[Indentura de battella portus de Athy]

This indenture maid at Abbirbroth the aucht day of the moneth of September the yeir of Gode ane thousande fywe hundreth and sex yeris

betuix ws George . . . abbot of . . . Abbirbroth . . . ande Thomas lorde of Innermeith ande baron of Innerkelor . . . beiris vitnes . . . as eftyr folowis . . . We George abbot forsaid with the consent of owr

conuent for hartly lufe we hawe to the saide lorde Thomas of owr fre wil gefis licens to the saide Thomas lorde to bryng ane fische boit in oure hawyn of Athy for al the dayis of his lywe · and his fischaris to pas and repas thairto with their stuf and geir fik as ganis tham ande to lay thair anchoris apon lande · to wis hyng ande dry nettis · to tak fische · ande all othir necefl'ar thingis to do vse exers and hant neidful to fisching craft ande sawyng of the boit and geir · quhilk vse sal induce na pofl'effione to the saide lorde of Innermeith nothir grunde rycht nor seruitute bot sal be alwais without preiudice or hurt til ws owr conuent ande place of Abbir· Α broth and owre success'ouris eftir the dede of the saide Thomas lorde · In witnes heirof to a part of this indenture to ramane with ws . . . the seille of Thomas lorde forsaid is 'appendit · ande to the part . . . to ramane with the said Thomas lorde we hayf appendit the commone selle of our ehaptour . . . befor thir witnes - mastyr Hew Dowglace dene of Brechin · Alexander Hepburn of Quhitfim · Adam Hepburn of the Crage knycht · Aleiander Guthre of that ilk · J ames Haye 'of N achtane knyeht · Robert Gray sone to lord Gray · John Ogilwy of the Crage ·

mastixfi Dauid Carale ande mastir James Farchar notairis · with othiris diuers.
